CAPSTONE PROJECT REPORT
Security Awareness Phishing Simulation
1. Introduction

Cybersecurity threats such as phishing attacks continue to be one of the most effective methods used by attackers to compromise user credentials, distribute malware, and gain unauthorized access. This project focuses on creating and executing a Security Awareness Phishing Simulation to evaluate user awareness, identify weaknesses, and train users on safe email practices.

2. Project Objectives

To design and deploy a realistic phishing simulation.

To assess user susceptibility to phishing attempts.

To analyze user behavior (clicks, login attempts, report rate).

To provide awareness training based on findings.

To document all findings with evidence and mitigation strategies.

3. Project Scope
In Scope

Creating a phishing scenario (email + landing page).

Sending controlled phishing emails to selected test users.

Monitoring clicks, credentials, and report behaviors.

Incident response simulation based on user actions.

Out of Scope

Real-world credential harvesting.

Targeting users without consent.

Exploit-based attacks.

4. Tools and Technologies Used
Purpose	Tool
Phishing simulation	GoPhish
Email template creation	HTML/CSS
Landing page hosting	Localhost / Python server
User tracking	GoPhish analytics
Screenshot capture	Snipping tool
Reporting	MS Word / PDF
